# Product Development Methodology (Project Overlay)

The universal lean wave-based delivery methodology — waves as intent, thin-slices as atomic outcomes, sprints as immutable bridges, hypothesis cards, bidirectional sprint close, intent-not-history doc style — is in the `praxis` plugin's `lean-delivery-guardrails` always-on instruction. Read it first.

The detailed runbooks are in the plugin skills:

- Wave creation → `create-wave`
- Wave product design spec → `create-product-design-spec`
- Wave product architecture spec → `create-product-architecture-spec`
- Wave quality spec → `create-quality-spec`
- Code contribution intake → `intake-code-contribution`
- Sprint creation → `create-sprint`
- Sprint close → `close-sprint`
- ADR → `create-adr`
- Pyramid Test Strategy → `test-by-ownership`

For the project-specific overlay (paths, gates, project alias personas), see the matching `.github/skills/<skill>/SKILL.md` files in this repo.

## Project-specific paths

| Artifact | Location |
|---|---|
| Wave docs | `{{paths.waves}}/wave-NNN-<slug>/` |
| Sprint docs | `{{paths.sprints}}/SPRINT.<ID>-<slug>.md` |
| Dashboard | `{{paths.product_dashboard}}` |
| Project context | `{{paths.project_context}}` |
| ADRs | `{{paths.adr}}/` |
| Use cases / personas | `{{paths.product}}/use-cases.md` |
| Themes | `{{paths.product}}/themes/` |

## Project-specific gates (in addition to the plugin's universal gates)

- All four wave files (`README.md`, `product-design.md`, `product-architecture.md`, `qa.md`) must exist and be reviewed before any sprint opens against the wave.
- Implementation cannot start until code contribution intake identifies the wave, thin-slice, sprint bridge, current code touchpoints, and red/green test posture.
- Sprint cannot close without `{{quality_gates.lint}}`, `{{quality_gates.format}}`, `{{quality_gates.type_check}}`, and `{{quality_gates.test}}` all passing.
- Dashboard is updated in the same commit as wave / sprint state changes.

## Persona ownership

| Phase | Owner |
|---|---|
| Wave intent + thin-slices | `.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product_designer}}.agent.md` |
| Wave architecture | `.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.principal_engineer}}.agent.md` |
| Wave registration + sprint sequencing | `.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product_manager}}.agent.md` |
| Sprint implementation | `.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.principal_engineer}}.agent.md` |
| Sprint close | `.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product_manager}}.agent.md` (with the engineering and design owners on each shore) |
